# 📦 Stocx Inventory Management Backend

## Version: 0.0.1

## 📖 Overview

Stocx is a minimal backend API for an Inventory Management System.
The goal of version `0.0.1` is to provide a simple, functional foundation with:

* Basic authentication (admin only)
* CRUD operations for inventory items
* Simple quantity management

This version focuses on **core functionality only**, with no advanced inventory features.

---

## 🎯 Goals

* Build a stable backend foundation
* Enable admin to manage inventory items
* Keep the system simple and extendable
* Support iterative development

---

## 👤 Users

### Admin (Single User)

* Full access to all APIs
* Can manage inventory items
* No role system (only one admin user exists)

---

## ⚙️ Core Features

---

### 🔐 Authentication

* User registration and authentication
* JWT-based authentication
* Refresh token support
* OTP-based email verification (no verification links)
* Protected routes using middleware

#### Endpoints

```
POST   /api/v1/auth/register
POST   /api/v1/auth/login
POST   /api/v1/auth/logout
GET    /api/v1/auth/current-user
POST   /api/v1/auth/change-password
POST   /api/v1/auth/refresh-token
POST   /api/v1/auth/verify-email-otp
POST   /api/v1/auth/forgot-password
POST   /api/v1/auth/reset-password/:resetToken
POST   /api/v1/auth/resend-email-otp
```

#### Notes

* OTP (One-Time Password) is sent to email for verification
* No verification links are used
* OTP expiry and retry limits should be enforced
* Secure password hashing (bcrypt)
* Access + Refresh token mechanism

---

### 📦 Inventory Management (CRUD)

#### Features

* Create item
* Get all items
* Get single item
* Update item
* Delete item

#### Endpoints

```
POST   /api/v1/items
GET    /api/v1/items
GET    /api/v1/items/:itemId
PUT    /api/v1/items/:itemId
DELETE /api/v1/items/:itemId
```

---

### 🔢 Quantity Management

* Quantity stored directly in item
* Can be updated via update API

#### Example

```
Initial quantity = 100
Update → quantity = 120
```

---

### 📊 Dashboard (Basic)

Provides simple inventory summary.

#### Endpoint

```
GET /api/v1/dashboard/summary
```

#### Response Includes

* Total number of items
* Total quantity across all items

---

### ❤️ Health Check

#### Endpoint

```
GET /api/v1/health
```

